#. <section class="sutta" id="an9.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.38:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.38:0.2"
msgid "4. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "4. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 38. Lokāyatikasutta → lokāyatikabrāhmaṇasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Lokāyatikasutta"
msgstr "38. Brahmin Cosmologists"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an9.38:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho dve lokāyatikā brāhmaṇā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then two brahmin cosmologists went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings "
"with him."

msgctxt "an9.38:1.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnā kho te brāhmaṇā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one "
"side and said to the Buddha:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli4.429"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an9.38:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Pūraṇo, bho gotama, kassapo sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ ñāṇadassanaṃ "
"paṭijānāti:"
msgstr ""
"“Master Gotama, Pūraṇa Kassapa claims to be all-knowing and all-seeing, to "
"know and see everything without exception, thus:"

msgctxt "an9.38:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Knowledge and vision are constantly and continually present to me, while "
"walking, standing, sleeping, and waking.’"

msgctxt "an9.38:2.3"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

msgctxt "an9.38:2.4"
msgid "‘ahaṃ anantena ñāṇena anantaṃ lokaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘With infinite knowledge I know and see that the world is infinite.’"

#. VAR: Ayampi → ayampi hi (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an9.38:2.5"
msgid ""
"Ayampi, bho gotama, nigaṇṭho nāṭaputto sabbaññū sabbadassāvī aparisesaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ paṭijānāti:"
msgstr ""
"And the Jain leader Nāṭaputta also claims to be all-knowing and all-seeing, "
"to know and see everything without exception, thus:"

msgctxt "an9.38:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘carato ca me tiṭṭhato ca suttassa ca jāgarassa ca satataṃ samitaṃ "
"ñāṇadassanaṃ paccupaṭṭhitan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Knowledge and vision are constantly and continually present to me, while "
"walking, standing, sleeping, and waking.’"

#. VAR: So → sopi (?)
msgctxt "an9.38:2.7"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says:"

# Here the MS reading is obviously wrong. Also see BB’s interesting note, which establishes that this is, in fact, a misrepresentation of Mahavira’s views.
msgctxt "an9.38:2.8"
msgid "‘ahaṃ anantena ñāṇena anantaṃ lokaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ viharāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘With infinite knowledge I know and see that the world is finite.’"

msgctxt "an9.38:2.9"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ, bho gotama, ubhinnaṃ ñāṇavādānaṃ ubhinnaṃ aññamaññaṃ "
"vipaccanīkavādānaṃ ko saccaṃ āha ko musā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"These two claim to speak from knowledge, but they directly contradict each "
"other. Which one of them speaks the truth, and which falsehood?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an9.38:3.1"
msgid "“Alaṃ, brāhmaṇā."
msgstr "“Enough, brahmins."

msgctxt "an9.38:3.2"
msgid "Tiṭṭhatetaṃ:"
msgstr "Leave this aside:"

msgctxt "an9.38:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘imesaṃ ubhinnaṃ ñāṇavādānaṃ ubhinnaṃ aññamaññaṃ vipaccanīkavādānaṃ ko "
"saccaṃ āha ko musā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘These two claim to speak from knowledge, but they directly contradict each "
"other. Which one of them speaks the truth, and which falsehood?’"

msgctxt "an9.38:3.4"
msgid "Dhammaṃ vo, brāhmaṇā, desessāmi, "
msgstr "I will teach you the Dhamma. "

msgctxt "an9.38:3.5"
msgid "taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "an9.38:3.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho te brāhmaṇā bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes sir,” those brahmins replied."

msgctxt "an9.38:3.7"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

# I don’t think we should include gatiya as BB, since it is not mentioned in what follows.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli4.430"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an9.38:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇā, cattāro purisā catuddisā ṭhitā paramena javena ca "
"samannāgatā paramena ca padavītihārena."
msgstr ""
"“Suppose there were four men standing in the four directions. Each of them "
"was extremely fast, with an extremely mighty stride."

#. VAR: daḷhadhammā → daḷhadhammo (sabbattha)
#. VAR: tālacchāyaṃ → tālacchātiṃ (si, s1-3, pts1) | tālacchādiṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an9.38:4.2"
msgid ""
"Te evarūpena javena samannāgatā assu, seyyathāpi nāma daḷhadhammā dhanuggaho "
"sikkhito katahattho katūpāsano lahukena asanena appakasirena tiriyaṃ "
"tālacchāyaṃ atipāteyya;"
msgstr ""
"They’re as fast as a light arrow easily shot across the shadow of a palm "
"tree by a well-trained expert archer with a strong bow."

msgctxt "an9.38:4.3"
msgid ""
"evarūpena ca padavītihārena, seyyathāpi nāma puratthimā samuddā pacchimo "
"samuddo "
msgstr ""
"Their stride was such that it spanned from the eastern ocean to the western "
"ocean. "

msgctxt "an9.38:4.4"
msgid "atha puratthimāya disāya ṭhito puriso evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Then the man standing in the east would say:"

msgctxt "an9.38:4.5"
msgid "‘ahaṃ gamanena lokassa antaṃ pāpuṇissāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘I will reach the end of the world by travelling.’"

msgctxt "an9.38:4.6"
msgid ""
"So aññatreva asitapītakhāyitasāyitā aññatra uccārapassāvakammā aññatra "
"niddākilamathapaṭivinodanā vassasatāyuko vassasatajīvī vassasataṃ gantvā "
"appatvāva lokassa antaṃ antarā kālaṃ kareyya."
msgstr ""
"Though he’d travel for his whole lifespan of a hundred years—pausing only to "
"eat and drink, go to the toilet, and sleep to dispel weariness—he’d die "
"along the way, never reaching the end of the world."

msgctxt "an9.38:4.7"
msgid "Atha pacchimāya disāya … pe …"
msgstr "Then the man standing in the west …"

msgctxt "an9.38:4.8"
msgid "atha uttarāya disāya …"
msgstr "Then the man standing in the north …"

msgctxt "an9.38:4.9"
msgid "atha dakkhiṇāya disāya ṭhito puriso evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "Then the man standing in the south would say:"

msgctxt "an9.38:4.10"
msgid "‘ahaṃ gamanena lokassa antaṃ pāpuṇissāmī’ti."
msgstr "‘I will reach the end of the world by travelling.’"

msgctxt "an9.38:4.11"
msgid ""
"So aññatreva asitapītakhāyitasāyitā aññatra uccārapassāvakammā aññatra "
"niddākilamathapaṭivinodanā vassasatāyuko vassasatajīvī vassasataṃ gantvā "
"appatvāva lokassa antaṃ antarā kālaṃ kareyya."
msgstr ""
"Though he’d travel for his whole lifespan of a hundred years—pausing only to "
"eat and drink, go to the toilet, and sleep to dispel weariness—he’d die "
"along the way, never reaching the end of the world."

msgctxt "an9.38:4.12"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an9.38:4.13"
msgid ""
"Nāhaṃ, brāhmaṇā, evarūpāya sandhāvanikāya lokassa antaṃ ñāteyyaṃ daṭṭheyyaṃ "
"patteyyanti vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"I say it’s not possible to know or see or reach the end of the world by "
"running like this."

msgctxt "an9.38:4.14"
msgid ""
"Na cāhaṃ, brāhmaṇā, appatvāva lokassa antaṃ dukkhassa antakiriyaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"But I also say there’s no making an end of suffering without reaching the "
"end of the world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an9.38:5.1"
msgid "Pañcime, brāhmaṇā, kāmaguṇā ariyassa vinaye lokoti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"These five kinds of sensual stimulation are called the world in the training "
"of the noble one."

msgctxt "an9.38:5.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an9.38:5.3"
msgid "Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā;"
msgstr ""
"Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "an9.38:5.4"
msgid "sotaviññeyyā saddā … pe …"
msgstr "Sounds known by the ear …"

msgctxt "an9.38:5.5"
msgid "ghānaviññeyyā gandhā …"
msgstr "Smells known by the nose …"

msgctxt "an9.38:5.6"
msgid "jivhāviññeyyā rasā …"
msgstr "Tastes known by the tongue …"

msgctxt "an9.38:5.7"
msgid ""
"kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā;"
msgstr ""
"Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "an9.38:5.8"
msgid "ime kho, brāhmaṇā, pañca kāmaguṇā ariyassa vinaye lokoti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"These five kinds of sensual stimulation are called the world in the training "
"of the noble one."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an9.38:6.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, brāhmaṇā, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "an9.38:6.2"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇā, ‘bhikkhu lokassa antamāgamma, lokassa ante viharati’."
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who, having gone to the end of the world, "
"meditates at the end of the world."

msgctxt "an9.38:6.3"
msgid "Tamaññe evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Others say of them:"

msgctxt "an9.38:6.4"
msgid "‘ayampi lokapariyāpanno, ayampi anissaṭo lokamhā’ti."
msgstr "‘They’re included in the world, and haven’t yet left the world.’"

#. VAR: Ahampi hi → ahampi (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.38:6.5"
msgid "Ahampi hi, brāhmaṇā, evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "And I also say this:"

msgctxt "an9.38:6.6"
msgid "‘ayampi lokapariyāpanno, ayampi anissaṭo lokamhā’ti."
msgstr "‘They’re included in the world, and haven’t yet left the world.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli4.431"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an9.38:7.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇā, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ "
"jhānaṃ …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who, as the placing of the mind and keeping it "
"connected are stilled, enters and remains in the second absorption …"

msgctxt "an9.38:7.2"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …"
msgstr "third absorption …"

msgctxt "an9.38:7.3"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr "fourth absorption."

msgctxt "an9.38:7.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇā, ‘bhikkhu lokassa antamāgamma lokassa ante viharati’."
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who, having gone to the end of the world, "
"meditates at the end of the world."

msgctxt "an9.38:7.5"
msgid "Tamaññe evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Others say of them:"

msgctxt "an9.38:7.6"
msgid "‘ayampi lokapariyāpanno, ayampi anissaṭo lokamhā’ti."
msgstr "‘They’re included in the world, and haven’t yet left the world.’"

msgctxt "an9.38:7.7"
msgid "Ahampi hi, brāhmaṇā, evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "And I also say this:"

msgctxt "an9.38:7.8"
msgid "‘ayampi lokapariyāpanno, ayampi anissaṭo lokamhā’ti."
msgstr "‘They’re included in the world, and haven’t yet left the world.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an9.38:8.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇā, bhikkhu sabbaso rūpasaññānaṃ samatikkamā "
"paṭighasaññānaṃ atthaṅgamā nānattasaññānaṃ amanasikārā ‘ananto ākāso’ti "
"ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who, going totally beyond perceptions of form, "
"with the ending of perceptions of impingement, not focusing on perceptions "
"of diversity, aware that ‘space is infinite’, enters and remains in the "
"dimension of infinite space."

msgctxt "an9.38:8.2"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇā, ‘bhikkhu lokassa antamāgamma lokassa ante viharati’."
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who, having gone to the end of the world, "
"meditates at the end of the world."

msgctxt "an9.38:8.3"
msgid "Tamaññe evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Others say of them:"

msgctxt "an9.38:8.4"
msgid "‘ayampi lokapariyāpanno, ayampi anissaṭo lokamhā’ti."
msgstr "‘They’re included in the world, and haven’t yet left the world.’"

msgctxt "an9.38:8.5"
msgid "Ahampi hi, brāhmaṇā, evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "And I also say this:"

msgctxt "an9.38:8.6"
msgid "‘ayampi lokapariyāpanno, ayampi anissaṭo lokamhā’ti."
msgstr "‘They’re included in the world, and haven’t yet left the world.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an9.38:9.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇā, bhikkhu sabbaso ākāsānañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘"
"anantaṃ viññāṇan’ti viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who enters and remains in the dimension of "
"infinite consciousness. …"

msgctxt "an9.38:9.2"
msgid ""
"sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma ‘natthi kiñcī’ti ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati … pe …"
msgstr "the dimension of nothingness …"

msgctxt "an9.38:9.3"
msgid ""
"sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr "the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "an9.38:9.4"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇā, ‘bhikkhu lokassa antamāgamma lokassa ante viharati’."
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who, having gone to the end of the world, "
"meditates at the end of the world."

msgctxt "an9.38:9.5"
msgid "Tamaññe evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Others say of them:"

msgctxt "an9.38:9.6"
msgid "‘ayampi lokapariyāpanno, ayampi anissaṭo lokamhā’ti."
msgstr "‘They’re included in the world, and haven’t yet left the world.’"

msgctxt "an9.38:9.7"
msgid "Ahampi hi, brāhmaṇā, evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "And I also say this:"

msgctxt "an9.38:9.8"
msgid "‘ayampi lokapariyāpanno, ayampi anissaṭo lokamhā’ti."
msgstr "‘They’re included in the world, and haven’t yet left the world.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli4.432"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an9.38:10.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, brāhmaṇā, bhikkhu sabbaso nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma "
"saññāvedayitanirodhaṃ upasampajja viharati, paññāya cassa disvā āsavā "
"parikkhīṇā honti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, take a mendicant who, going totally beyond the dimension of "
"neither perception nor non-perception, enters and remains in the cessation "
"of perception and feeling. And, having seen with wisdom, their defilements "
"come to an end."

msgctxt "an9.38:10.2"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇā, ‘bhikkhu lokassa antamāgamma lokassa ante viharati "
"tiṇṇo loke visattikan’”ti."
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who, having gone to the end of the world, "
"meditates at the end of the world. And they’ve crossed over clinging to the "
"world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an9.38:10.3"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
